<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>image tag</title>
    <link rel="stylesheets" href="./style.css">
    <style>
        p{
            color: red;
            font-size: 25px;
            background-color: black;
        }
    </style>    
</head>
<body>
     <p>CSS- cascading style sheets

        To make webpages attractive
        
        Background color, font size, font color, borders, margins, padding,
        
        We can css in html page in three ways:
        
        1. Inline css: beside html elements we will style
        
        2. Internal css: we will add style tag in head
        
        3. External css: we create new css file and add in html using link</p>
</body>
</html>
